summary: My name is Manel Fornells, and I am 24 years old. I was born in Paris and lived in Andorra until I moved to Barcelona. After being awarded a Bachelor of Arts with Honours (First Class and first of my promotion), I moved to Amsterdam to pursue my dream of becoming a film composer. I was fortunate and honored to be accepted as a Masters’ student in “Composing for Film” at the Conservatorium van Amsterdam. This Master closely collaborates with the Nederlandse Filmacademie (NFA), and thanks to it, I was involved in various significant collaborations and scored several documentaries, fiction films, and animated shorts. On top of meeting new people and getting to know the Dutch ways, I grew as a musician and composer by tackling many different musical styles, always keeping in mind the movies' dramatic needs and necessities. My journey as a film composer is only getting started, and I can already say that it will be epic.
